.TH "pci_walk_bridge" 9 "pci_walk_bridge" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_walk_bridge \- walk bridges potentially AER affected
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" pci_walk_bridge
.BI "(struct pci_dev *bridge "  ","
.BI "int (*cb)(struct pci_dev *, void *) "  ","
.BI "void *userdata "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bridge" 12
bridge which may be a Port, an RCEC, or an RCiEP
.IP "cb" 12
callback to be called for each device found
.IP "userdata" 12
arbitrary pointer to be passed to callback
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the device provided is a bridge, walk the subordinate bus, including
any bridged devices on buses under this bus.  Call the provided callback
on each device found.

If the device provided has no subordinate bus, e.g., an RCEC or RCiEP,
call the callback on the device itself.
